        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-09T12:57:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I am also enjoying the 2013 whites, which are often quite open already, but there is quite a bit of botrytis in some of the wines, especially those from Chassagne, that gives them a honeyed, musky quality that some may not appreciate. The 2013 Ramonet Boudriotte is the most obvious example of this that I\u2019ve had lately.</p>",
